The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 India to tour Bangladesh from May 7

Dhaka: India will play two Tests and three one-day Internationals in a three-week tour of Bangladesh from May 7, cricket officials announced on Sunday. 

The Board of Control for Cricket in India (BCCI) has verbally accepted the schedule sent by us for the countrys tour to Bangladesh in May 2007, the Bangladesh Cricket Board (BCB) announced in a statement. 

The itinerary would be announced later, BCB chief executive officer Mahmudur Rahman said. 

India, who played the first Test against newcomers Bangladesh in 2000, will start the tour by playing the one-dayers, follwed by the Tests. 

Bangladesh have played two home series against India, but have yet to tour India for a Test series. 

The BCB chief executive said both the sides had discussed the issue and would soon announce dates for a Bangladesh tour of India. 

India last visited Bangladesh in December 2004 when they lost a one-day game in Dhakas Bangabandhu National Stadium, handing Bangladesh their first-ever home success. (Agencies) 




